Interface Filter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BasicFilter, NotFilter

    public interface Filter
    An interface that captures what it means to be a filter.

    • Method Detail

      • matches

        boolean matches(twitter4j.Status s)
        Returns true if the filter matches the given tweet
        Parameters:
        s - the tweet to check
        Returns:
        whether or not the tweet matches this filter

      • parse

        static Filter parse(java.lang.String queryString)
        This static method parses the given input string and creates a Filter that represents the query. If the input doesn't match the rules for a filter that contains "and", "or", and/or "not" operators, it is treated as a literal string to match.
        Parameters:
        queryString - the string containing the filter expression
        Returns:
        a Filter that represents that filter condition

      • terms

        java.util.List<java.lang.String> terms()
        Get all the terms (strings in basic filters) used in this filter. When we query the Twitter API, we must indicate all the terms we are interested in, and this allows us to collect them up for each active query.
        Returns:
        a list of terms mentioned in this filter
